<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-08-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-08-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.12155/150: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-17T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>183. Your 154, August 13, 9 a.m. In view of reported attitude of Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs Department desires you in your discretion either to
                            bring matter to personal attention of President or to request Foreign
                            Minister to take such action. Emphasis should be placed upon recent
                            losses on both sides of border due to floods and upon urgent necessity
                            for contemplated works to prevent recurrence such damages.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
